rComments: Great class, great professor. Teaching is definitely what he should be doing!
A nice person, but quite inexperienced (even though not the worst) at teaching. Could be quite harsh to deal with if you are inexperienced with this kind of a professor.

This professor definitely deserves a much higher grade! After 4 years at this school and 30 odd classes, I genuinely feel like he is one of the best professors I've had! Classes are super organized, systematic and easy to do well. Very open to regrades, organizes student discussions outside class in office hours and is very passionate about PolSci!

The prof wasn't necessarily bad, just disorganized with his lectures and slides. You kind of never know what to write down or not. The weekly paper thing was excessive too. I have a feeling this was mostly because of his inexperience with teaching though because he does know what he's talking about.

This professor is excellent at introducing the main theories of IR and GPE. In every lecture, he goes over the theories for the topic of the week (e.g. global finance). Outside the classroom, Malcolm is very available to chat and assigns homework in such a way as to maximize learning. That said, I he sets the bar quite high for expectations.
